Assert that x is a valid SummarizedExperiment

assert_is_valid_sumexp.Rd

Assert that x is a valid SummarizedExperiment

assert_is_valid_sumexp(x, .xname = get_name_in_parent(x))

Arguments

x

SummarizedExperiment
.xname

see assertive.base::get_name_in_parent

Value

TRUE or FALSE

Examples

# VALID
    file <- download_data('halama18.metabolon.xlsx')
    x <- read_metabolon(file, plot = FALSE)

#> 	Read: ~/autonomicscache/datasets/halama18/halama18.metabolon.xlsx
#> 		Infer design from sample_ids
#> 		Guess replicate values from sampleids: ctrl_h10_R1 => R1
#> 		Log2 transform
#> 	Add PCA
#> 		Retain 391/391 features: non-zero, non-NA, and non-NaN for some sample
#> 		Run limma
    assert_is_valid_sumexp(x)
# NOT VALID
    rownames(SummarizedExperiment::colData(x)) <- NULL
    # assert_is_valid_sumexp(x)
